<p>
Here are some other resources that might be helpful:
</p>

<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="https://sketchplanations.com/">Sketchplanations - Simplifying complex ideas in sketches</a> - This is amazing <i>and</i> Jono keeps coming up with more.</li>
<li><a href="https://illustratedlife.substack.com/p/icon-practice-and-building-visual">Icon Practice and Building Visual Vocabulary - by Amy Cowen</a> - also check out the rest of <a href="https://illustratedlife.substack.com/">Amy's blog</a></li>
<li><a href="https://visualframeworks.com/">visual frameworks – A language of patterns</a> - great for visual metaphors</li>
<li><a href="https://thenounproject.com/">The Noun Project</a> - useful for getting unstuck</li>
<li><a href="https://bikablo.com/en/tools/">Bikablo visual dictionaries and learning tools</a> (there's a quick flip-through of <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4EbdAWDeIOg">Thinking with Your Pen</a>)</li>
